    <head>
        <title>Getting started with Dynalist</title>
        <flavor>dynalist</flavor>
        <source>https://dynalist.io</source>
        <ownerName>Eckhard</ownerName>
        <ownerEmail>e.pfluegel@gmail.com</ownerEmail>
    </head>
    <body>
        <outline text="Hello there, thanks for using Dynalist! This document contains the essentials to get you started. Keep it as a reference, and you can also add your own notes on how to use Dynalist."/>
        <outline text="The Essentials List" _note="Check things off after you have tried them!" checkbox="true">
            <outline text="Dynalist is all about nested lists. `Tab` to go a level deeper, and `Shift+Tab` to come back"/>
            <outline text="When you put your mouse on a list item, a hamburger menu icon and a magnifying glass icon will show up">
                <outline text="Click on the magnifying glass to &quot;zoom in&quot; on that item"/>
                <outline text="Click on the menu for a number of other options (this menu is called the item menu)"/>
            </outline>
            <outline text="Convert lists to checklists by choosing &quot;Make checklist&quot; in the item menu or `Ctrl+Alt+C`"/>
            <outline text="You can sort list items by dragging their bullet points (works for multiple items too!)"/>
            <outline text="You can select multiple items as well! Simply drag the mouse to select"/>
            <outline text="Create a new document by clicking on the &quot;+&quot; icon in the header of the left sidebar"/>
            <outline text="Right click on a document for a list of things you can do with it"/>
            <outline text="Add a note to an item by pressing `Shift+Enter`" _note="You can go back to the item using the same shortcut"/>
            <outline text="Use the `!` trigger to open the date picker and add dates" _note="Make sure to type it after a space"/>
            <outline text="(Optional) If you previously use WorkFlowy, you can import from WorkFlowy by choosing the option in the main menu in the top right corner"/>
        </outline>
        <outline text="The Max Efficiency List" _note="Check things off after you have tried them!" checkbox="true">
            <outline text="Use #tags to group things"/>
            <outline text="Use `Ctrl+O` to quickly jump between documents"/>
            <outline text="Bookmark a place by clicking on the star, you can go back to it later very quickly in the bookmark pane" _note="Access the bookmark with the shortcut `Ctrl+Shift+B`"/>
            <outline text="To insert a link to another item, type `[[` and start searching for items to add"/>
            <outline text="There are keyboard shortcuts for almost everything, use `Ctrl+?` to bring up the cheatsheet!"/>
        </outline>
        <outline text="Need help?">
            <outline text="In the master menu (the one on the top right of this page), choose &quot;Feedback&quot; and we'll reply asap"/>
            <outline text="You can also check out [our help center](http://help.dynalist.io/)"/>
        </outline>
    </body>
</opml>
